The paper discusses algorithms for optimizing the trajectories of mobile sensors, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of linear Gaussian assumptions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses applications in gas concentration mapping and target tracking, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
